{"question": "What is the variance of the dot product of the queries and keys when their components are independent random variables with mean 0 and variance 1?", "answer": "The variance of the dot product of the queries and keys, when their components are independent random variables with mean 0 and variance 1, is \\( d_k \\) (where \\( d_k \\) is the dimensionality of the queries and keys). This is derived from the fact that the dot product \\( q \\cdot k = \\sum_{i=1}^{d_k} q_i k_i \\) has mean 0 and variance \\( d_k \\) (as stated in the retrieved evidence, CHUNK bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:9).", "sources": [{"chunk_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:9", "page_number": 4, "document_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697", "source_filename": "attention_is_all_you_need.pdf", "region_ids": ["region_35"], "crop_asset_ids": [], "score": 0.1828}, {"chunk_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:8", "page_number": 4, "document_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697", "source_filename": "attention_is_all_you_need.pdf", "region_ids": ["region_34", "region_35", "region_36", "region_37", "region_38", "region_39", "region_40", "region_41", "region_42", "region_43"], "crop_asset_ids": ["asset_region_40"], "score": 0.1219}, {"chunk_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:18", "page_number": 9, "document_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697", "source_filename": "attention_is_all_you_need.pdf", "region_ids": ["region_101", "region_102", "region_106", "region_107", "region_108", "region_109"], "crop_asset_ids": ["asset_region_101"], "score": 0.1}, {"chunk_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:20", "page_number": 10, "document_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee072818