{"question": "What is the role of the encoder in the described model architecture?", "answer": "The role of the encoder in the described model architecture is to map an input sequence of symbol representations to a sequence of continuous representations, denoted as z = (z1, ..., Zn). This transformation allows the decoder to subsequently generate an output sequence of symbols (y1, ..., Ym) one element at a time. The encoder processes input embeddings with positional encoding, which is essential for understanding the order of the input sequence (CHUNK bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:5, CHUNK bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:6).", "sources": [{"chunk_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:5", "page_number": 2, "document_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697", "source_filename": "attention_is_all_you_need.pdf", "region_ids": ["region_15", "region_18", "region_22", "region_24"], "crop_asset_ids": [], "score": 0.95}, {"chunk_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:6", "page_number": 3, "document_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697", "source_filename": "attention_is_all_you_need.pdf", "region_ids": ["region_25", "region_26", "region_27", "region_28", "region_29", "region_30", "region_31", "region_32"], "crop_asset_ids": ["asset_region_27"], "score": 0.85}, {"chunk_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:3", "page_number": 2, "document_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697", "source_filename": "attention_is_all_you_need.pdf", "region_ids": ["region_13", "region_14", "region_16", "region_19", "region_21", "region_23"], "crop_asset_ids": [], "score": 0.75}, {"chunk_id": "bdfaa68d8984f0dc02beaca527b76f207d99b666d31d1da728ee0728182df697:chunk:18", "page_number": 9, "document_id": "bdfaa68d898